1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. a3 Bxc3+ 5. bxc3 b6
{ This variation usually transposes to  5...Nc6  line. Whether it is better @@StartBracket@@for Black@@EndBracket@@ to start  5...b6  or  5...Nc6  is not easy to say.You will find @@StartBracket@@in your database@@EndBracket@@ more games to have had  5...b6  , but  5...Nc6  move order was the one chosen by the World champion Magnus Carlsen!In both cases, my mainline for White is  6.f3  and leads @@StartBracket@@should lead@@EndBracket@@ to the same line. White's main alternative to  6.f3  is  6.Bg5  . }
6. Bg5
{ Definitely an alternative for White! This move has been @@StartBracket@@just@@EndBracket@@ little played and Black can easily go wrong! }
6... h6 7. Bh4 Nc6
{ White has an interesting new idea  (never tested before!)  probably leading to a promising pawn sacrifice. }
8. Qc2
{ White follows on his regular plan @@StartBracket@@pushing e4, taking space as fast as he can@@EndBracket@@, only willing to do it while keeping his f-pawn still on its initial square. }
8... Ba6 9. e4
{ Black now needs to solve h4-d8 diagonal pin and he needs to solve it in a radical way }
9... g5 10. Bg3
{ Here Black is best advised to take the white dark squared bishop. } 10... Nh5
{ 10...Na5  wins a pawn, but leads to a better position for White after  11.h4  Nh5  12.Be5  f6  13.Be2!  The black knight will be awkwardly placed on  g7  13...Ng7  14.Bg3  Bxc4  15.hxg5  fxg5  16.Bxc4  Nxc4  17.Nf3  Black paid a high price for 'pawn collection' and his pieces are poorly coordinated. White has more than 'just compensation'. }
11. Be2
{ We now see the advantage of white pawn still being on f2. Black must react immediately. }
11... Nxg3 12. hxg3 Na5
{ Now White goes for a typical Saemisch-type pawn sacrifice, often seen in several Saemisch lines. }
13. c5 Bxe2 14. Qxe2 bxc5
{ Black will be a pawn up, but his king will not have a safe place to go to, while his knight is not stable. }
15. Nf3 Qe7 16. O-O
{ White has more space, safer king, good piece coordination, and definitely has sufficient compensation here. Does he have more... it's not easy to say. }
