12... c5
{ With this move Black wants to fix White's c4-weakness. White is quick with active play, not minding sacrificing a pawn. }
13. Bd3 Nb6 14. f4 { In the case of } 14... Naxc4
{ White has an easy solution in } 15. Qe2 Na5 16. fxe5 dxe5 17. Rb5
{ White gets his pawn back and is clearly better. } 17... Nc6 18. Rxc5 *

