6. e3
{ It is not played often, it was tried long ago by Smyslov and it is definitely a good alternative for White.White will push e4, just like in our mainline, but will refrain from playing the move f3, giving himself in some lines a chance for a queen sortie with Qg4.The lines/positions we get are unexplored and certainly interesting for a player willing to take his opponent 'off the book' at a very early stage of the game.How should Black react? The most logical, and my mainline, is to follow his 'regular development strategy' in the variation 5...Nc6 then prepare ...Ba6, ...Nc4 thus attacking white's c4 pawn. }
6... b6 7. Bd3 Na5 8. e4
{ We have the same position from our main line, but White's pawn is still on f2, which may bring White some advantages @@StartBracket@@for example the queen sortie Qg4@@EndBracket@@. }
8... Bb7
{ Now White can opt for interesting novel positions involving a pawn sacrifice. }
9. Qe2
{ 9.f3  leads to our main line, as Black does not have anything better than to focus on White's  c4  weakness and play  9...Ba6  transposing.  We have already on move 9@@StartBracket@@!!@@EndBracket@@ a new position, according to my database only seen before in an internet blitz game. Most likely critical @@StartBracket@@and the most logical@@EndBracket@@ for assessing the feasibility of White's idea is the continuation where Black 'goes for a pawn'. }
9... Nb3 10. Rb1 Nxc1 11. Rxc1 Qe7
{ White does not have to sacrifice his a3 pawn, but it is in the spirit of the system not to waste time defending it and to put the emphasis on 'space taking & quick development'! }
12. Nh3 Qxa3 13. O-O
{ We have a position that is not easy to evaluate. Your computer's engine will give you zeros.Black will have to return his queen to square e7, which means that capturing the pawn cost him two tempi. The third world champion Jose Raul Capablanca once said: 'a single pawn is not worth three tempi'.... and here Black has already lost two tempi.White has a space advantage, will push his f-pawn and play for the attack on the king. It will take some time before Black's extra pawn starts to count.The white player entering this position should be happy with his space advantage and not be worried about being one pawn down. }
