{ For White in general has a good idea of developing his knight to f3 and also take more space, and this is exactly what White does! }
9. f4 { This is probably the way White should play. } 9... Ba6 10. e5 Nd7 11.
Qe2 Qe7 12. Be3 f5 13. Nf3
{ White is in a good situation here, he has a space advantage, white does not need to worry about protecting the c4-pawn weakness. White was better in Byrne, R -Keres, P Moscow 1955. }
