[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. a3 Bxc3+ 5. bxc3 c5
{ This is one of the mainlines of the Saemisch. In some opening manuals  5...c5  is even considered Black's best response.White has to choose between  6.e3  @@StartBracket@@and then push e4@@EndBracket@@ or a more direct  6.f3  , pushing e4 directly on the next move. Both lines have been played by many great players.I have analysed and played both and come to the conclusion that only  6.f3  gives White good prospects of gaining an opening advantage. }
6. f3
{ In case of  6.e3  comes a headache position.  6...Nc6  7.Bd3  O-O  8.Ne2  b6  9.e4  Ne8  10.O-O  Ba6  11.f4  f5  We have many high level @@StartBracket@@the highest@@EndBracket@@ games where this position has been tested.White failed to demonstrate any advantage along the way and often found himself in trouble; he lost because his initiative stopped, while the weakness of the  c4  pawn remained.I don't have any fresh ideas to bring to this line, I think Black is at least ok and so I suggest the reader play  6.f3! }
6... Nc6
{ In some opening manuals this line is even considered the main one in the Saemisch. I will give some of Black's alternatives. }
7. e4
{ Black has a 'coffee houses' line, which is not at all good for Black, but should still be mentioned. }
7... cxd4 8. cxd4 Nxe4
{ Black gets three pawns for his knight, but lands in a bad position. } 9. fxe4
Qh4+ 10. Kd2 Qxe4 11. Nf3 Nxd4
{ Here the most practical for White is probably to go into the endgame. } 12.
Bd3 Nxf3+ 13. Qxf3 Qxf3 14. gxf3
{ Black's problem here is that he cannot develop nor coordinate his pieces and will at some stage start losing his pawns. }
14... b6 15. a4 Bb7 16. Ke3 f6
{ White has different good ways here. One logical plan is to fix Black's potential a7-pawn weakness. }
17. a5 Kf7 18. a6 Bc6 19. Ba3
{ It might be at first glance that this position doesn't look as bad for Black as it actually is... but the situation is terrible.Black simply cannot develop, White will at some point push to c5, open the queen's side and capture the black pawn a7.To give the reader an idea of the advantage, the computer gives about +4. }
