{ White is threatening mate in one, while black Ne8 needs to protect c7-square }
22... h6
{ regardless of the relatively limited material left, we have plenty of tactics in the position. }
23. Bxh6 gxh6 { Loses to } 24. Rf8+ Kh7 25. O-O-O
{ And White wins Black's Ne8 and should win, due to material advantage. } 25...
Bxc4 26. Rd7+ Kg6 27. Re7
{ Winning the knight. This is an easy win for White. } *

