{ My engine indicates  17.Nf5  with Qg5 threat to be even stronger. } 17... Nd7
18. f4
{ White is rolling his pawns, the attack plays itself. The game continued  18...Qa4  19.Bb2  Na5  20.Qf3  Next to having a weak king, Black will also have problems defending his d5-pawn.  20...Qb3  21.Bc3  Rac8  22.Ne2  Qb5  23.f5  Nf6  24.a4!  Qa6  25.Nf4  Black loses his d5 pawn and the game is soon over; Sokolov, I - Maze, S Budva 2009. 1-0 @@StartBracket@@29@@EndBracket@@ Sokolov, I @@StartBracket@@2657@@EndBracket@@-Maze, S @@StartBracket@@2579@@EndBracket@@ Budva 2009 }
