16... Ba4 { Black does not really have active play. } 17. Rb4 Bd7 18. Bd2 Rab8
19. Rb2 Nc6
{ Black does not have any threats and White has different options here. } 20.
Nd5+ Kf7
{ In the game Volkov, S @@StartBracket@@2648@@EndBracket@@-Jens, J @@StartBracket@@2409@@EndBracket@@ Kemer 2007, White released the pressure with  21.Nxc7  .  Though White went on to win, I prefer moves like }
21. Be3
{ Here the situation is not easy for Black. Taking the white knight  21...exd5  will obviously give White a great compensation after  22.cxd5  while living with this knight on d5 is not easy. }
