1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. a3 Bxc3+ 5. bxc3 c5 6. f3 d5 7. cxd5 Nxd5 8.
dxc5 Qa5 9. e4 Ne7 10. Be3 O-O 11. Qb3
{ Definitely White's main and probably best move. } 11... Qc7
{ Black's most played @@StartBracket@@and also probably the best@@EndBracket@@ answer. Black wants 12...Nd7 followed by ...Nxc5. }
12. Bb5
{ White stops Black's  12...Nd7  @@StartBracket@@threat is  13.Bxd7  @@EndBracket@@. }
12... Nec6 13. Ne2 Na5 14. Qb4
{ We have many games here and Black struggles. White will make his strategic exchange, namely his Bb5 for Nb8. Black struggles to get back his pawn.Normally this position seems to me to be open to two outcomes. Black needs to push ...e5 to activate his bishop. }
14... e5 15. O-O Na6 { This allows the good strategic trade. } 16. Bxa6 bxa6
{ Here we have a number of high-level games. White has no obvious path to the advantage, but Black struggles.White has three basic ideas here:a. exchange sacrifice on d5;b. piece sacrifice on d4;c. simply give back the c3 pawn to win time to coordinate pieces and play with a better pawn structure. }
17. Qa4
{ Sacrificing the c3-pawn in order to win time to coordinate pieces can be done with  17.c4!?  Be6  18.Rfd1  Rab8  19.Qe1  and White should have somewhat better prospects.   17.Rad1  Be6  18.Rd5  An exchange sacrifice; your computer will indicate Black's most accurate defense, which was also played by Jakovenko  18...Rfb8!  @@StartBracket@@  18...Rab8  19.Qa4  Bxd5  20.exd5  Rb5  21.d6  Qc6  22.Ng3  Rxc5  23.Qg4  Rc4  24.Nf5  Rxg4  25.Ne7+  Kh8  26.Nxc6  Rxg2+  27.Kxg2  Nxc6  28.Rd1  and White went on to win in Vidit, S - Vaibhav, S, Xingtai 2019.@@EndBracket@@   19.Qa4  Bxd5  20.exd5  Rb5!  21.Rd1  Rxc5!  22.Bxc5  Qxc5  23.Kh1  Qb5!  24.Qe4  f5!=  and the game later ended in a draw in Li, C-Jakovenko, D Geneva 2017. }
17... Be6
{ If  17...Bd7  18.Qc2  Be6  White can opt for  19.c4!  Now White goes for a piece sacrifice on  d4  . }
18. Nd4 { Black was not in the mood to take the White knight. } 18... exd4
{ Or  18...Bc4  19.Rfb1  exd4  20.cxd4  Bb5  21.Qc2 } 19. cxd4 Bb3 20. Qb4
{ White has sufficient compensation. Whether it is more is not easy to say. } *

